Build a functional web app that reproduces the core behavior of https://searchqualityrater.com/ but with no styling emphasis. Use plain, clean HTML structure and minimal default browser styling only. Do not spend time on visual design, animations, gradients, shadows, rounded UI polish, or branding. Focus on logic, structure, scoring, and output.

## Goal
Create a tool called **Search Quality Rater Score** that lets a user enter a URL, analyzes the page against a rubric modeled on Google's Search Quality Evaluator Guidelines, and returns:
- an overall score out of 100
- category-level scores
- pass/fail or scored checks under each category
- concise explanations for each check
- actionable recommendations
- a structured final summary

## Core Functionality
The app must support these flows:

